Description: Fragment of flattened, tapering handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine rose-pink; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 44? Name Damophilos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0232.47?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1052)
